<subSubSection id="8D9386C8944BFFE51AE2F8DDFB38F8BA" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C536D543944BFFE51AE2F8DDFBD0F8F2" blockId="2.[151,1436,1729,2008]" box="[199,1034,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944BFFE51AE2F8DDFE94F8F2" bold="true" box="[199,334,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to its relatively common occurrence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C536D543944BFFE51AE2F8FAFB38F8BA" blockId="2.[151,1436,1729,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944BFFE51AE2F8FAFE15F891" bold="true" box="[199,463,1837,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Locality and horizon.</emphasis>
Amber mine located near Noije Bum Village, Tanai Township, Myitkyina District, 
<collectingRegion id="074D1BA1944BFFE51AB2F885FEF0F8BA" box="[151,298,1874,1900]" country="Myanmar" name="Kachin" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Kachin State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BD9E95D3944BFFE51B10F885FE7CF8BA" box="[309,422,1874,1900]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
; unnamed horizon, mid-Cretaceous, Upper Albian to Lower Cenomanian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D9386C8944BFFE51AE2F8A2FC25F80E" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C536D543944BFFE51AE2F8A2FC25F80E" blockId="2.[151,1436,1729,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944BFFE51AE2F8A2FE98F859" bold="true" box="[199,322,1909,1935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body approximately 2.6 times as long as wide (versus 2.1 times as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944BFFE51EC3F8A0FA46F846" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[1254,1436,1910,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944BFFE51EC3F8A0FA46F846" box="[1254,1436,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Bipogonia fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944BFFE51AB2F84DFF2AF862" bold="true" box="[151,240,1946,1972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A944BFFE51AB2F84DFF2AF862" box="[151,240,1946,1972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Prosternum moderately broad, about 1.2–1.3 times as wide as long (versus 1.7 times as wide as long in 
<taxonomicName id="0289AEC0944BFFE51FA1F84CFF08F80E" authority="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Kundrata &amp; Huang &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Artematopodidae" genus="Bipogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944BFFE51FA1F84CFF08F80E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">B. fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944BFFE51AFCF869FEE9F80E" bold="true" box="[217,307,1982,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECCEB42A944BFFE51AFCF869FEE9F80E" box="[217,307,1982,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Metaventral discrimen distinct only posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C6944BFFE5194DF869FC18F80E" box="[872,962,1982,2008]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1503,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1436,181,1480]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Details of Bipogonia trivialis Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179428, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, ventral view. B, Prothorax, ventral view. C, Mesothorax, ventral view. D, Mid leg. E, Metathorax and abdominal base, ventral view. F, Elytral and abdominal apices, showing the interlocking tongue (arrowhead). G, Head, dorsal view. H, Pronotum and antenna, dorsal view. I, Elytron, dorsal view.Abbreviations: a1–11, antennomeres 1–11; cl, clypeus; ep, elytral epipleuron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtc, metacoxa; mttc, metatrochanter; mtv, metaventrite; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500935/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Figs 3E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="5DB2C9C6944BFFE519EBF869FC28F80E" box="[974,1010,1982,2008]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,955,979]" captionTargetBox="[223,1365,181,931]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[223,1365,181,931]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bipogonia trivialis Li, Kundrata &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., paratypes. A, B, NIGP179429, under incident light. A, Dorsal view. B, Ventral view. C, D, NIGP179430, under widefield fluorescence. C, Head, dorsal view. D, Elytral apices, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="91F685CB944AFFE41AB2FC22FD30FBE7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500931" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500931/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="260" startId="3.[151,250,1013,1037]" targetBox="[347,1241,179,988]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="C536D543944AFFE41AB2FC22FD30FBE7" blockId="3.[151,1437,1013,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="260">
