<subSubSection id="8D9386C8944DFFE31AE2F92AFE18F87E" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" type="description">
<paragraph id="C536D543944DFFE31AE2F92AFE18F87E" blockId="4.[151,1437,1789,1960]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="F7FD0951944DFFE31AE2F92AFE83F8C1" bold="true" box="[199,345,1789,1815]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">Description.</emphasis>
As for the genus, except for the following characters: Body moderately broad, 
<quantity id="027178A6944DFFE31EF0F929FA86F8CE" box="[1237,1372,1790,1816]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="4.4">4.4–4.6 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="027178A6944DFFE31AB2F8F5FEFEF8EA" box="[151,292,1826,1852]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.7">1.7–1.8 mm</quantity>
wide. Eyes well-developed, without interfacetal setae. Prosternum moderately broad. Surface of elytron with 10 puncture rows. Mesocoxal cavities separated by about twice the shortest diameter of coxal cavity. Metaventral discrimen distinct only near posterior end, not clearly visible anteriorly.Abdominal ventrite 5 about 1.7 times as long as ventrite 4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
